column27: DavidB (http://www.gnxp.com/blog/2007/03/on-reading-wright.php) makes the following useful observation: \There are two important omissions from the collection SPE. For reasons of length it does not contain Wright's 5-part 1921 paper on 'Systems of Mating'
column28: which is the foundation of all his later writings.. Fortunately
column29: all 5 parts of the paper are available free online [present contributor link
column30: http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/?term=Wright%2C+Sewall%20-%201921%20-%20Systems%20of%20Mating]. The other major omission from SPE is that there is no substantial piece on Wright's technique of path analysis. This is Wright's major contribution to statistical theory
column31: and he constantly makes use of the technique. Fortunately
column32: many of his papers on path analysis are also available online
